Description: Sliver of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay medium-coarse gritty brown. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 102, 49? From same die as a piece from Kaunos, B.Schmaltz, Die Hellenistischen Amphorenstempel vom Kaunos (Asia Minor Studien 79) 87, KA 203. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0310.32.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1706)
